## 4. Root cause — exact call chain

```
api/service.py:810          preprocessed_data.rt_replannable = rt_replannable   ← flags set HERE
api/service.py:811          preprocessed_data.ct_replannable = ct_replannable
          │
          ▼
api/service.py:1115         solve_with_checkpointing(partitioner, partitions,    ← flags NOT passed
                              constraint_values, objective_weights,
                              job_id=..., ...)
          │
          ▼
solver/checkpoint_manager.py:396   def solve_with_checkpointing(...)              ← no rt/ct params in signature
solver/checkpoint_manager.py:495   sub_result = partitioner.solve_partition(...)  ← no flags forwarded
solver/checkpoint_manager.py:551   result = partitioner.solve_partition(...)      ← no flags forwarded
          │
          ▼
solver/partitioner.py:615   def solve_partition(self, partition,                   ← no rt/ct params
                              constraint_values, objective_weights,
                              incoming_state=None)
solver/partitioner.py:650   preprocessed = preprocess_data(                        ← fresh PreprocessedData
                              demands_data, resources_data, absences_data)           no flags set
solver/partitioner.py:664   model = create_and_solve_model(preprocessed, ...)
          │
          ▼
solver/model.py:420-421     lc06_active = (... and (getattr(self.data,            ← reads False
                              'rt_replannable', False) or getattr(self.data,
                              'ct_replannable', False)))
solver/model.py:437-438     rt_replannable = getattr(self.data,                    ← reads False
                              'rt_replannable', False)
                            ct_replannable = getattr(self.data,
                              'ct_replannable', False)
solver/model.py:473-475     print("  [LC_06_rest_days_allocation] Skipped         ← the symptom
                              (rt_replannable=False and ct_replannable=False)")
```

Confirmed with:
```
grep -n "rt_replannable\|ct_replannable" solver_v2/api/service.py \
  solver_v2/solver/model.py solver_v2/solver/partitioner.py \
  solver_v2/solver/checkpoint_manager.py
```

`solver/checkpoint_manager.py` returns 0 matches — the flags never transit through it.

**Non-partitioned path is unaffected.** At `service.py:1153`, `create_and_solve_model(preprocessed_data, ...)` is called with the top-level object that has the flags stashed. However, this path only fires when `demands ≤ 500` AND `days ≤ 60` (see `config.py:116-117`). Any realistic production payload will partition. The TC-02 payload did.

