## 8. Retest — TC-02 with a reduced payload (max 2 months, narrower scope)

Per the user's instruction to keep future runs under 2 months and lower resource counts, use this reduced TC-02 payload. It still exceeds partition thresholds so the bug site is exercised.

### 8.1. Why 2 months (not 1)

Partitioning fires when `demands > 500` OR `days > 60` (`config.py:116-117`). A 1-month run with narrow team scope may drop below 500 demands and skip partitioning — then a "pass" would NOT prove the fix works. A 61-day range forces day-based partitioning regardless of demand count. This is the minimum-size payload that provably exercises the regression site.

### 8.2. Retest payload (T-BOTH-RETEST)

Save to `/tmp/payload-tc02-retest.json`:

```json
{
  "user_id": "javi_test",
  "test_mode": false,
  "use_mock_data": false,
  "plan_range": {"start_date": "2026-05-01", "end_date": "2026-06-30"},
  "target_team_ids": [],
  "target_group_ids": [],
  "lock_allocations": true,
  "locked_date_ranges": [{"start": "2026-05-01", "end": "2026-06-30", "reason": "Sprint freeze"}],
  "replannable_demand_type": ["RT Jour de repos", "CT Jour de compensation"],
  "options": {"time_limit_seconds": 5400}
}
```

Notes:
- 61 days (2026-05-01 → 2026-06-30 inclusive is 61 days). Forces partitioning.
- `time_limit_seconds=5400` (90 min) — reduced from 7200. The original TC-02 solved in 557s so 5400s is ample buffer.
- Leaves `target_team_ids=[]` (all teams). If you want to go even smaller, add specific team IDs you know contain RT/CT data — query the external DB assignments endpoint filtered by team to pick candidates.
- Still includes both `RT Jour de repos` and `CT Jour de compensation` — this is the whole point.

Size estimate: a 2-month planning range with all teams is roughly 2× the TC-02 demand count. If that takes too long, add team filters in `target_team_ids`; the partition threshold for days (61 > 60) will still fire even with fewer demands.

